---
title: Mandarin Chili Chicken with Rice & Roasted Zucchini-Carrot Medley
description: There's something about coming home to a pork chop dinner that’s so old-school satisfying. And this one’s got some new-school flavors: garlicky roasted carrots and zucchini with a crusty, pan-seared chop and a sweet, savory, and bright mandarin-chili sauce. It’s all served over fluffy cooked rice, sprinkled with scallion greens and more velvety sauce. School’s out!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6682e8c888a40e5df74250a5-f5bb1a13.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/668583a49a3c9af871e5c756-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mandarin-chili-chicken-668583a49a3c9af871e5c756
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 78 g
  sugar: 29 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1740 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Halve @mandarin orange{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss zucchini and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

While veggies roast, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together juice from whole mandarin, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{2%oz}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, half the @cornstarch{1%tbsp}, @water{1/2%cup}, and @sugar{1%tsp}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Swap in chicken or salmon for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook salmon (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, 5-7 minutes, then flip and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for pork over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and soft, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add mandarin chili sauce. Reduce heat to medium; cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce begins to thicken, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Add pork to sauce and turn to coat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice and veggies between plates. Top rice with pork and drizzle with any remaining sauce. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.